history.content:
CS162 takes it to the next level in terms of projects so keep that in mind. However, week to week CS162 isn't bad (unless there's a project).

CS186 in the past has been an "easy" class so to speak, but this semester the projects have gotten considerably harder/longer. Week to week for CS186 was low work load when I took it and it seems like this semester it is about that same.

To summarize, those classes are extra hard when there is a project deadline coming up but week to week it's not bad.

If you are planning on taking a 3rd class you should probably make it a non-technical class.

If I found taking 61C and 70 together to be decently hard, but doable, can the same be said about taking 162 and 186 together? I just want to see if 186 is a good class to take with 162. I am signed up for both, and have heard that 186 is no longer an "easy" CS upper div because the projects end up taking a good amount of time/design. If any one has any input, that would be awesome!
history.subject: Taking CS162 and CS186 together
